parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Engine Oil Consumption and Engine Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine failure, stalling, and loss of power, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded. Engine failure can also result in costly repairs or even require replacement.
symptoms: white smoke or black smoke from the exhaust

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trunk latch can cause the trunk to become stuck or difficult to open, which can lead to inconvenience and potential safety issues, such as being unable to access emergency equipment or luggage.
symptoms: a clicking noise is heard when attempting to open the trunk
